HEADWORD: Scambler
<hw>Scam"bler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>1. One who
scambles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bold intruder upon the hospitality of others; a
mealtime visitor.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scamblingly</ent>⟦br⟧
